***No new probable or suspected cases reported in the past 24 hours**
Daily Report on Number of SARS Cases on the Chinese Mainland (8 Jun
2003) MOH, P.R.China 8-June-03
From: 1 Nov 2002 To: June 8, 2003, BJT 10:00
Province: cumulative no. cases/ no. new cases/ no. recovered/ no.
deaths/ no. suspected cases
Beijing: 2522/ 0/ 1543/ 184/ 550
Hebei: 215/ 0/ 197/ 12/ 0
Inner Mongolia: 283/ 0/ 216/ 29/ 20
Liaonin: 7/ 0/ 2/ 2/ 1
Shanghai: 8/ 0/ 3/ 2/ 0
Shanxi: 448/ 0/ 379/ 23/ 3
Sichuan: 20/ 0/ 16/ 2/ 1
Total: 5328/ 0/ 4057/ 339/ 663
Note: the total figure includes the latest numbers of SARS cases in
the other 19 SARS-affected regions, namely, Heilongjiang, Xinjiang,
Gansu, Jiangsu, Anhui, Shaanxi, Zhejiang, Henan, Chongqing, Jiangxi,
Ningxia, Shandong, Fujian, Hunan, Guangdong, Jilin, Tianjin, Hubei
and Guangxi. In total, the 19 regions had reported 1825 cumulative
confirmed SARS cases, 88 suspected cases, 1699 discharged patients,
49 [are now] under medical treatment as well as 85 deaths.
