Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) Update
Toronto - Listed below is the Ministry of Health and Long-Term Care's
SARS statistical update, as of Sunday 8 Jun 2003.
Key facts:
68 active probable cases (5 cases related to the first cluster)
68 active probable hospital cases
250 discharged/recovered as of today
33 deaths as of today (25 cases related to the first cluster)
176 other persons under investigation (as a precautionary measure,
these persons receive the same treatment as probable and suspect
cases)
Probable cases in last 10 reported days
